description.1: A cavalcade of crazy capers starring Marvel's most flappable fowl! First, Howard teams up with the Grey Panther! Then, terrors of the night beware -- the vengeance of DUCKMAN!
description.4: Daredevil tries to figure out why the Mauler is after his old boss...
description.6: Civil War breaks out amongst the Changelings! Will Hulk's peers accept his help in their direst hour?
description.7: Tony battles against Force and a wave of Justin Hammer's men.
description.8: GHOST RIDER is back, and he's ready for vengeance! Can Johnny Blaze stop a deadly ritual in time to save its captive?
description.11: The FF must find the source of a red mist that is engulfing New York City...and causing them all to lose control of their powers!
description.12: Spidey uncovers the dark, ulterior endgame of Belladonna. Roderick Kingsley beware!
description.16: Hellcat is forced to confront the sudden loss of her mother. Meanwhile, Matt Murdock is attacked by Mandrill, who’s looking for revenge against The Defenders!
description.18: The Empire Strikes Back adaptation roars on as the Millenium Falcon attempts to escape the Imperial fleet!
description.23: Madame Web's first appearance! Spider-Man seeks out Debra Whitman's clairvoyant after he finds her image at the scene of a kidnapping. But not all is as it appears, especially at the scene of the crime. Madame Web shows Spider-Man the truth with her powers of precognition! And Spider-Man begins his tutelage with Madame Web!
description.24: Following the battle with Marcus, son of Immortus and Carol Danvers, the Avengers must rebuild the mansion. What strange discoveries will Wasp make in Yellowjacket's lab? And why is Jarvis wielding a vacuum cleaner as a weapon?
description.25: Captain America reflects over his many years as America's living legend! Witness the shocking ending to The Mercenary and the Madman! The dream begins now!
description.28: When a town is threatened by a ghost from the past, The Spirit of Vengeance is the only one who can set things right!
description.29: The Changelings have kidnapped Betty Ross and Rick Jones! Can Hulk retrieve his friends, or will his efforts be unwelcome once again?
description.30: Tony has his hands full with not only Bethany Cabe, but Madame Masque! Iron Man is under attack by Masque and two of her Dreadnoughts. He's also un-helmeted. Will Rhodey arrive in time to save the day?
description.31: Witness the ongoing adventures of Marvel's fastest, deadliest soldier for hire - DOMINIC FORTUNE!
description.32: Scotty is not only alive and well…he now has super powers! But all may not be as it seems!
description.34: Hulk falls into battle formation with girlfriend Jarella by his side. What if Jarella had never perished, and Hulk found his calling as a Barbarian Warrior? Plus, Aunt May as a costumed hero? Unbelievable, perhaps, but when bitten by a radioactive spider, that's exactly what happens!
description.35: Can the power of love overcome a love of power? Will young Franklin be freed of his possession from Nicholas Scratch?
description.36: Spider-Man goes on a wild goose chase to find out who is behind the Prowler impersonation.
description.38: The First Appearance of Calypso!  Kraven the Hunter and Calypso are here, and they're craving Spider-Man's head! Debra Whitman confides in Peter, appealing to his strengths as Spider-Man. Kraven demands a duel with Spidey...so long as it appears on the Globe's front page!
description.39: After going through a nine month gestation in a matter of days, Ms. Marvel gives birth to a baby boy named Marcus. But within hours of his birth, Marcus is an adult male with the ability to build complex machinery. What strange, alien forces are at play? Who is Marcus? And what is the mysterious machine that he feels so compelled to build?
description.40: He may be the nation's champion, but is Captain America fit to be its leader? Find out when Captain America runs for President!
description.41: It's the battle of Hoth in this The Empire Strikes Back adaptation.
description.43: Little do Spider-Man and Black Widow know, ""opposing"" gangs they're both targeting are actually banding together. Spider-Man's senses start tingling that this isn't going to be an average crime-fighting night….
description.44: Clea and Wong are taken prisoner in the Mirror Realm!
description.45: Nighthawk gets good news about his legal troubles. Hulk runs into an old friend who desperately needs his help.
description.51: Hulk enters a game of "monsters and kings" in this king-sized special!
description.54: Gladiator holds a group of kids hostage in a museum and Daredevil has to take him down in time to make it to Foggy's wedding.
description.55: Hell-Bats attack Johnny while he rides through a mysterious town, but that's nothing that a little hellfire can't fix!
description.56: The Gamma Base crew must aid a wounded centaur that's arrived at their cabin's doorstep. And from there...things only get stranger!
description.57: Iron Man battles two Madame Masque-controlled Dreadnought robots.
description.58: The Human Fly attacks Spider-Woman risks Scotty's life!
description.60: If Phoenix must die, she's not going out alone. Cyclops fights side by side with Jean Grey in this emotional, epic image by John Byrne.
description.61: It's all fun and games until...Franklin gets possessed by Nicholas Scratch in the Negative Zone!
description.62: After The Cobra breaks out of prison, Spidey's got more trouble than he can handle!
description.64: Hyperion betrays the Nth Command when he vows to stay by Thundra's side!
description.67: A secret commission has been monitoring the Defenders, but their intentions may not be in the best interest of the heroes.
description.74: Kicking off the first part of The Empire Strikes Back adaptation!
description.75: The birth of Fusion! Twin brothers Hubert and Pinky Fusser lead drastically different lives; Hubert is a scientist at a research firm, while Pinky is the janitor for that firm. After one of Hubert's radiation experiments goes awry, the brothers merge into one energized being! Spider-Man takes on the energy-absorbing blasts of Fusion...and their dual personalities!
description.76: After defeating Red Ronin with the help of Wonder Man, the Avengers return to the Mansion and are stunned to find Wanda and a heavily-pregnant Carol. And although Ms. Marvel has only been pregnant for a few days, she is ready to deliver at any moment!
description.77: Cap's battle with Dragon Man continues! Once Captain America starts to gain the upper hand on Dragon Man, things take a turn for the worse when he finds himself going up against the Thing, Magneto, and Spider-Man?
description.80: Johnny is drinking to drown his sorrows and keep his inner demon at bay, but it's going to take more than that to stop the Spirit of Vengeance!
description.81: Just as Bruce warms up to a beautiful woman, Silver Surfer confronts our hero with a plan to stop Galactus!
description.82: A Stark Enterprise team activates a new sonic drilling rig and it inadvertently explodes. Iron Man sets out to rescue the Stark employees.
description.84: Spider-Man arrives to bring Spider-Woman to justice!
description.86: Victor Von Doom is considered one of Marvel's worst villains. But what if the tables were turned and public opinion swayed? Doctor Doom goes against Mephisto, and becomes the world's favorite hero!
description.87: A grief-stricken Cyclops holds the lifeless body of Jean Grey as the rest of the X-Men look on in sadness.  John Byrne's cover shows the love and loss that the conclusion of the "Phoenix Saga" brought to Xavier's band of mighty mutants.
description.88: Sue discovers more about the alien creatures who are threatening the earth's magnetic poles. She also discovers their vast history on our planet!
description.90: Mutant villain Mesmero has decided to go straight...by becoming a Broadway producer! But when critics pan Mesmero's lackluster (and all-around strange) show, this baddie-at-heart may resort to mind control. Mesmero not only wants the praise of critics, he wants to convince Spider-Man to star in his next death-defying production!
description.91: Attack of the Red Ronin! The Wasp and Yellowjacket are horrified to discover that the massive automaton destroying New York is none other than deranged scientist Dr. Earl Cowan!
description.92: He's back! Dragon Man is on the loose once again and that means bad news for Cap, as he finds himself literally in the beast's clutches.
description.93: Luke and Leia encounter a living organic ship...can they solve the mystery in time?
description.94: The Scarlet Witch joins the Thing and Stingray in their mission to take back the Serpent Crown...which has since been seized by Roxxon Oil owner Hugh Jones!
description.95: A cab driving Howard the Duck teams up with the Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man to take down Status Quo, a villain notoriously opposed to fads and subliminal messaging from mass media!
description.96: Clea has gone missing in her search for Wong. Desperate to find her, Strange enters another world where a band of barbarians, (who seem to be led by Clea), are ready to execute him!
description.97: When stolen sound-canceling technology from Wakanda hits the streets of New York, Black Panther and the Defenders can only try and stop the pandemonium!

0.text: Vance Astro threatens the fabric of space-time by trying to alter his past! Thing and the rest of the Guardians of the Galaxy must stop him before history is re-written!

1.text: A cavalcade of crazy capers starring Marvel's most flappable fowl! First, Howard teams up with the Grey Panther! Then, terrors of the night beware -- the vengeance of DUCKMAN!

2.text: Welcome to the X-Men Kitty Pryde...hope you survive the experience.  Plus, Alpha Flight shows up looking for Wolverine.

3.text: She-Hulk meets some of her biggest foes…but this time in COURT!

9.text: Dr. Karl Malus uses mind control technology to pit the Werewolf by Night against Spider-Woman!

17.text: Before he was the macabre Moon Knight, he was mercenary Marc Spector. Witness the origin of the hero known as Moon Knight! Cloaked in the spirit of the Egyptian moon god, Moon Knight swears vengeance on “Bushman”, the mercenary who takes innocent lives and leaves his colleagues for dead.

19.text: Captain Fate and his piratical crew return! And Man-Thing may not fare so well in their second showdown!

20.text: Mandy must be stored away in Sir Denis’s Scottish castle to protect her from assassins!

26.text: Following the events of the Dark Phoenix Saga, the X-Men lay Jean Grey to rest.  After losing the woman he loves, Cyclops quits the X-Men -

27.text: Jennifer Walters is a lawyer by day, She-Hulk by night. But what happens when these two sides begin to clash?

42.text: A villain from the X-Men's past has kidnaped the high-flying Angel and Ben Grimm. Now, the odd-couple heroes must navigate a treacherous maze full of death traps to confront their captor once and for all.

46.text: El Aguila is back! The rogue vigilante tails Power Man and Iron Fist to Canada where a plot of thievery is underway! Can the Heroes for Hire manage to solve a crime and defend themselves from this possibly dangerous threat?

47.text: The sinister Madame Menace procures Machine Man's arm with the intent to mass produce. That's a violation MM won't endure!

48.text: Black Jack Tarr enlists the help of Shang-Chi and Leiko to free his friend's sister.

51.text: Hulk enters a game of "monsters and kings" in this king-sized special!

53.text: She-Hulk vs. the King of the Swamp…the shambling Man-Thing!

60.text: THE FATE OF THE PHOENIX! It's the Shi'Ar versus the X-Men in an epic duel on the blue area of the Moon! Winner decides the fate of the Dark Phoenix! Can Cyclops save his love? Or is she doomed to die at the hand of the Shi'Ar?
If Phoenix must die, she's not going out alone. Cyclops fights side by side with Jean Grey in this emotional, epic image by John Byrne.

68.text: A corrupt fraternity sets their sights on destroying Man-Thing. Chemical warfare may be used against the muck-monster, and all of Cyprus County could be in serious trouble!

69.text: Shang-Chi and Leiko investigate reports of a monster terrorizing the citizens of Chinatown.

73.text: What is a planet without time? Captain Marvel seeks an answer!

79.text: Losing control of her irradiated side, She-Hulk goes on a desperate lam from the police!

83.text: Simon Williams’ first solo saga! The Hollywood Avenger vs. the mighty Dreadnought!

87.text: CHILDREN OF LIGHT AND DARKNESS! The Dark Phoenix has defeated the X-Men. Who remains with the power to oppose her? In a last ditch effort, Professor X enters the fray!

A grief-stricken Cyclops holds the lifeless body of Jean Grey as the rest of the X-Men look on in sadness.  John Byrne's cover shows the love and loss that the conclusion of the "Phoenix Saga" brought to Xavier's band of mighty mutants.

98.text: Shang-Chi is attacked by a street gang and decides to teach them a few things.
